notes.note: Rec'd estimate from L.J. Patterson for replacement of multiple components. Said the customer was driving down the trail and the wheel fell off. Provided pictures, you can see the wheel hub has thick steel backing that mounts onto axle. That is snapped off, still a piece sitting on the axle. Wheel hub is split in 3 different directions. Definitely not a manufacturer defect. Called Apex Cylce and provided pictures that were sent to me. Technicians theorize that the axle nut was over torqued and slightly cracked the hub, which then heated up while driving and caused the hub to severely crack, allowing the wheel to fall off. One technician there has 20 something odd years of experience on Polaris, says he has never seen that. Confirmed that Polaris definitely would not have covered this repair. Said it isn't even worth sending an email to Polaris to inquire. Turning this claim down. M.P.

notes.note:
Good afternoon, thank you for your previous email with the estimate for the replacement of the a/c compressor and tailgate handle on Ms. Mahara's F-150. Unfortunately her contract does not cover door handles, or items that have to be replaced as a result of the handle being broken. However, it will cover the replacement of the compressor. Please be advised, the customer is responsible for any diagnostic fees, shop supplies, and fluids (refrigerant and dye), as well as a $100 deductible. 

Additionally, you have requested $400 in labour between the charge for evac and recharge and the labour required to replace the compressor. Our Mitchell Labour Guide displays 3.5 hours for the compressor labour, and the labour to evac and recharge. 3.5 hours x $110/h = $385. This is the max we will be able to pay out for labour. If you wish to charge the quoted labour amount, the customer will be responsible for the difference. The payout is as follows:

Parts-$598.95
Labour-$385.00 (3.5 hours x $100/h)
Deductible-$100.00
Tax-$114.91
Authorization-CET89BMP19

Total = $998.86

Once the repair is complete, please send us a copy of the final invoice for payment.

Best regards,


Matthew Puls
Claims Adjuster

Thank you,
Michael
